{"title":"fix(vigil-app): correct image tag","body":"Root cause: Deployment/vigil-app specifies a non-existent Docker image tag "nginx:bad-tag-v9", causing ImagePullBackOff.

Evidence: `Warning Failed Failed to pull image "nginx:bad-tag-v9": rpc error: code = NotFound desc = failed to pull and unpack image "docker.io/library/nginx:bad-tag-v9": failed to resolve reference "docker.io/library/nginx:bad-tag-v9": docker.io/library/nginx:bad-tag-v9: not found`

Fix: Change image tag to `nginx:stable`."}
